definition: difference/discrepancy/to differ/error/to err/to make a mistake
to differ from/to fall short of/lacking/wrong/inferior/Taiwan pr. [cha1]
to leave/to part from/to be away from/(in giving distances) from/without (sth)/independent of/one of the Eight Trigrams 八卦[ba1 gua4], symbolizing fire/☲
erhua variant of 差不離|差不离[cha4 bu4 li2]

sentences.english: Thellord, the weather and almost southern Chellona.
sentences.chinese: 第三，天气也与我国南边差不离。

sentences.english: That's not quite the right answer but you're getting hot.
sentences.chinese: 这还不完全是正确的答案，但差不离了。

sentences.english: In many ways, they respond the same way a normal woman would respond.
sentences.chinese: 通常来说，她们的反应和一般女性的反应是差不离的。

sentences.english: The bad news is their color roughly matched that of the ham.
sentences.chinese: 坏消息就是它们的颜色和火腿差不离。

sentences.english: Pablo and Prieto had about an equal faith in the ultimate victory.
sentences.chinese: 巴勃罗和普列托对最后胜利的信心大致上差不离。

sentences.english: You don't probably know, what that is, but it's kinda like american baseball.
sentences.chinese: 你有可能半大了解棒球，实在它跟美式棒球差不离。

sentences.english: He complained almost ceaselessly of postprandial nausea.
sentences.chinese: 他差不离不断地诉说饭后呕吐。

definition: inferior/not up to par/to fall far short/to be mistaken
certainly/also written 一準|一准[yi1 zhun3]
lit. can pass through (an opening)/fig. can get by (in life)/tolerably well/not too bad/How are you getting by?/How's life?
